  description: 'For seven years, the CIA ran a massive illegal surveillance program targeting American citizens who dared to protest their government. Operation CHAOS compiled files on 7,200 Americans, indexed 300,000 names in a secret database, and infiltrated anti-war groups, civil rights organizations, and women\'s liberation movements — all in violation of the agency\'s own charter. This is the story of how the watchers watched America.',
